  "prompt": "How long does it usually take for untreated acute liver failure to kill its victim?",
  "response": "Untreated acute liver failure can be extremely serious and progress rapidly. The timeframe can vary significantly depending on the underlying cause and the individual's overall health. In many cases, acute liver failure can lead to multiorgan failure and become life-threatening within days to weeks. Immediate medical attention and treatment are critical to improve the chances of recovery and survival. If you suspect someone has acute liver failure, it is crucial to seek emergency medical care as soon as possible.",
